```

So `sub nsw i32 %y, %x` decomposes to `%y - %x` (i.e., `%y` with coefficient +1, `%x` with coefficient -1).

Now, the condition is `icmp sgt i32 %sub, %z`. This gets normalized to `icmp slt i32 %z, %sub` (swapped). So we have `%z < %y - %x`, i.e., `%z + %x < %y`.

